subject: Fix broken installation task
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-05 09:33:13.000000000', 'files': ['tasks/tempest_install.yml', 'defaults/main.yml'], 'message': "Fix broken installation task

Currently, when you try to install os_tempest in a functional test the
installation of tempest fails as the 'Install pip packages for tempest
(no prebuilt venv)' task is doing a with_items that includes
tempest_git_dest, which is incorrect.  This commit updates the
with_items in that specific task and also sets two common defaults in
the defaults/main.yml file.

Change-Id: I08510e2e15ed9bec08b0878f416a42a3b5b7ed6c
"}]
commit_message:
Fix broken installation task

Currently, when you try to install os_tempest in a functional test the
installation of tempest fails as the 'Install pip packages for tempest
(no prebuilt venv)' task is doing a with_items that includes
tempest_git_dest, which is incorrect.  This commit updates the
with_items in that specific task and also sets two common defaults in
the defaults/main.yml file.

Change-Id: I08510e2e15ed9bec08b0878f416a42a3b5b7ed6c

commit_message:
Add option to clear information from ports

This patch adds the option of "no-fixed-ip" and
"no-binding-profile" which is used to clear the
fixed-ip and binding:profile information from the
ports.

revisions:

Closes-Bug: #1566321

Change-Id: I52447dea93ff2e6a32d597a632093661feed7c71
"}]
commit_message:
Support string index for list in get_param

Accept for string index like '1' for list in get_param function
For example, with lengths equal to [4,5,6]. We can write down something
like this: `length: {get_param: [lengths,'1']}`.
Closes-Bug: #1566321

Change-Id: I52447dea93ff2e6a32d597a632093661feed7c71

commit_message:
Dont pass tenant-id in request unless given

Currently, if tenant-id is not passed during tap-service-create,
it is passed as None.
This is not correct, tenant-id should be populated in the request
body only when it is passed as an attribute.

Change-Id: Idc6e117955a13f9aa70167e6997e83fca9bcae37
Closes-Bug: #1540739

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-09 17:05:37.000000000', 'files': ['.testr.conf'], 'message': "Modify default timeout for testr to 20 seconds

One thing we see every once in a while is crazy long
unit tests being introduced into Cinder.  Many times
this ends up being something goofy like a unit test
of a retry method that sleeps (without mocking sleep).

This patch drops the default timeout level from 60
seconds to 20.  Why 20?  Well, currently our longest
test averages about 10 seconds in the gate, I'd love to
drop this to 10 or 12, but to keep from havin the world
end, let's double that for safety, and revisit later
on how to get this down.

Ideally I'd love to target something like 10 seconds,
but that may not be realistic.

Change-Id: I0688afe6c24017368b058bffdfe260802f07e3ab
"}]
commit_message:
Modify default timeout for testr to 20 seconds

One thing we see every once in a while is crazy long
unit tests being introduced into Cinder.  Many times
this ends up being something goofy like a unit test
of a retry method that sleeps (without mocking sleep).

This patch drops the default timeout level from 60
seconds to 20.  Why 20?  Well, currently our longest
test averages about 10 seconds in the gate, I'd love to
drop this to 10 or 12, but to keep from havin the world
end, let's double that for safety, and revisit later
on how to get this down.

Ideally I'd love to target something like 10 seconds,
but that may not be realistic.

Change-Id: I0688afe6c24017368b058bffdfe260802f07e3ab

Trying to figure out what snapshots a volume has associated to it

commit_message:
Add snapshot ID's to volume detail view

Trying to figure out what snapshots a volume has associated to it
can be sort of a pain.  Currently you have to list snapshots and
grab parent volume-id's from there.  It's more common though that
a user would want to see what snapshots exist for a volume.

This patch just adds a list of snapshot ID's to the view builder
for volume detail (show).

APIImpact: Adds active_snapshots (list of snapshot IDs) to detailed view/response.

Change-Id: I1eddcc4c5d64459e5ac52cacf84bdfe8278ae6db

commit_message:
Add replicate by volume-type to SolidFire driver

This patch adds the needed methods to configure volume
replication based on volume-type on create, clone and
create from snapshot.

This adds methods to create volumes on a remote cluster
based on cluster_pairs info, creates the remote volumes
and enables pairing/replication between the "remote" and
the primary.

Additionally we also make sure we delete both the source
and dest on delete calls.

Finally, implement the get_replication_updates call.

To enable, the only required setting is replication_enabled.
The required base extra-specs entry is as follows:
    {u'replication_enabled': u'<is> True'}

Change-Id: I4fb6ee383d9f1ece026521f63b2c64567d91e495

commit_message:
Add cluster Pairing setup to SolidFire driver

Part of v2 replication requires setup of cluster
pairing based on config entries.

This patch adds the cluster pairing routines to
the driver init method and upon successful pairings
will set the replication_enabled capability to True.

The expected/required config entry in order to specify
a cluster-pairing is in the form of the replication_device
setting.

  replication_device =\
  device_target_id:AutoTest2-INsA-FOR-TEST-ONLY,\
  managed_backend_name:devcloud@solidfire2#solidfire2,\
  mvip:192.168.138.177,\
  login:admin,\
  password:admin

Change-Id: Id9246ff6c2b7b833b281d9f6e5f0c0656ce966a2

commit_message:
Use oslo-config-generator

Our config file generation is still incomplete, this patch
is an attempt to move over to using the oslo-config-generator.

There is an effort to create a version that auto-generates the
cinder/opts.py file which is awesome.  In the meantime however
we should have a working sample.conf generator until that work
is completed.

Co-Authored-By: Sergey Vilgelm <svilgelm@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I13ff90ce218ca56515a58d93364296cbee8c2631

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-08-29 00:08:04.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/manager.py', 'cinder/volume/drivers/solidfire.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_solidfire.py'], 'message': "Implement V2 replication capability in SolidFire

This change implements the Cinder V2 replication feature
in the SolidFire driver.

NOTE: This feature is still experimental, and is not intended
for production use during the L release for any driver including
SolidFire.  The primary purpose is to provide an experimental
implementation that can be tested and used as a reference.

To enable this feature:
The SolidFire driver currently only supports replicating to
managed backends.  In other words, another SolidFire cluster
that's configured in your OpenStack deployment (this can be
using either multi-backend, or seperate hosts).

The necessary config look like this:

enabled_backends = sf1,sf2

[sf1]
san_password = admin
san_login = admin
san_ip = 11.0.0.2
volume_driver = cinder.volume.drivers.solidfire.SolidFireDriver
volume_backend_name = sf1
secondary_backend = devbox@sf2#sf2
replication_devices = {'mvip'='11.0.0.9' 'login'='admin'\
                       'passwd'='admin'}

[sf2]
san_password = admin
san_login = admin
san_ip = 11.0.0.9
volume_driver = cinder.volume.drivers.solidfire.SolidFireDriver
volume_backend_name = sf2

This sets up cluster replication between sf1 and sf2, with sf1 being the
primary until a failover command is issued, at which time the host and
provider info entries for the failed over volume are updated and pointed
to the secondary cluster.

Running failover again, will swap the cinder primary back to the
original cluster again.

Change-Id: Ia39ae10fb412f90d4b22f312b83f33eb2fb45bef
"}]
commit_message:
Implement V2 replication capability in SolidFire

This change implements the Cinder V2 replication feature
in the SolidFire driver.

NOTE: This feature is still experimental, and is not intended
for production use during the L release for any driver including
SolidFire.  The primary purpose is to provide an experimental
implementation that can be tested and used as a reference.

To enable this feature:
The SolidFire driver currently only supports replicating to
managed backends.  In other words, another SolidFire cluster
that's configured in your OpenStack deployment (this can be
using either multi-backend, or seperate hosts).

The necessary config look like this:

enabled_backends = sf1,sf2

[sf1]
san_password = admin
san_login = admin
san_ip = 11.0.0.2
volume_driver = cinder.volume.drivers.solidfire.SolidFireDriver
volume_backend_name = sf1
secondary_backend = devbox@sf2#sf2
replication_devices = {'mvip'='11.0.0.9' 'login'='admin'\
                       'passwd'='admin'}

[sf2]
san_password = admin
san_login = admin
san_ip = 11.0.0.9
volume_driver = cinder.volume.drivers.solidfire.SolidFireDriver
volume_backend_name = sf2

This sets up cluster replication between sf1 and sf2, with sf1 being the
primary until a failover command is issued, at which time the host and
provider info entries for the failed over volume are updated and pointed
to the secondary cluster.

Running failover again, will swap the cinder primary back to the
original cluster again.

Change-Id: Ia39ae10fb412f90d4b22f312b83f33eb2fb45bef

commit_message:
Reordered builders in npm builds

Some of our npm builds are breaking because the cache has not yet
been updated by the time the npm-install macro runs. This patch
does two things - ensures that apt-get update is invoked before
prerequisites install, and reorder the builders in our javascript
templates to match that of the other jobs.

Change-Id: I44440c9da33eeb86d703ab4e605c31b02df1335c

commit_message:
Fix API end point for tapservice/tapflow

Due to the difference of API Endpoint and Resource Body,
NeutronClient could not succesfully create the tap-services
( and consecutively, tapflow).
The following code change modifies the API end point, and fixes
the problem with NeutronClient.

Change-Id: I9fa21bb273ef8a5c6fabece0a29673839cf8e945
Closes-Bug: #1539130

logs with "set -x".  Swizzle it off around the sensitive commands.

commit_message:
Add tests to OVN Native L3 gate job

Adding tests that should succeed to the OVN Native
L3 gate job.  Add to the exclude list the tests that
do not yet succeed.  Future patches will add back
in the excluded tests as they are made to succeed,
either by fixing the tests or devstack configuration
or by adding features to OVN Native L3.

Change-Id: I72895c5a942eb86575d67ce09e1163d2adee350e
Closes-bug: #1549862

Log SHA1 hash of X-Auth-Token value

Remove logging of sensitive information like the
token value from X-Auth-Token. Instead log the sha1
hash of the token value, prefixed with '{SHA1}'.

Conflicts:
	neutronclient/common/utils.py

Closes-Bug: #1367339
Change-Id: I72d2ff5ca569c942aa6896aeadab489ff0097255
(cherry picked from commit d8fa792ee720e7877fa371e69633546b752e73da)

token value from X-Auth-Token. Instead log the sha1
hash of the token value, prefixed with '{SHA1}'.

subject: Add recent/detail openstack-health api.
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-04-04 13:41:09.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_health/tests/test_api.py', 'openstack_health/api.py'], 'message': 'Add recent/detail openstack-health api.

Added a new api to retrieve the full details of the most recent runs, rather
than just the summary. This data was already available in the code, the api
simply returns it to the caller. This api can be used to provide “Test %”
complete rather than a simple “Runs passed/failed” which is in the current
/recent api.

Moved the existing functionality of the recent api call to a wrapper
module. This will be called by the recent api and the recent/detail api.
The detail version will return all the information returned by
subunit2sql and will not calculate pass or fail.

Added a unit test for the new recent/detail api.

Change-Id: I5528444148f525285cafed3fa9ce0a94dbfd5306
'}]
commit_message:
Add recent/detail openstack-health api.

Added a new api to retrieve the full details of the most recent runs, rather
than just the summary. This data was already available in the code, the api
simply returns it to the caller. This api can be used to provide “Test %”
complete rather than a simple “Runs passed/failed” which is in the current
/recent api.

Moved the existing functionality of the recent api call to a wrapper
module. This will be called by the recent api and the recent/detail api.
The detail version will return all the information returned by
subunit2sql and will not calculate pass or fail.

Added a unit test for the new recent/detail api.

Change-Id: I5528444148f525285cafed3fa9ce0a94dbfd5306

commit_message:
Document our policy on fixing v2.0 API bugs

There was recent discussion in some reviews about fixing
latent bugs in the legacy v2.0 API code. Since the
v2.0 API is deprecated and v2.1 is the default since Liberty,
we shouldn't need to fix latent low-priority bugs in v2.0
anymore.

However, we'll still fix critical bugs, and we shouldn't
knowingly introduce new regressions that would result
in a 500 response.

Change-Id: I9937d9226a99754dadcc48d599090296f5ae01f7

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-04-04 07:34:28.000000000', 'files': ['manifests/backend/vsphere.pp', 'spec/classes/glance_backend_vsphere_spec.rb'], 'message': 'Implement ability to pass CA bundle certificate for vCenter server

Glance with vsphere backend by default verifies vCenter server TLS/SSL
certificate using system truststore (e.g.
/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt). Here is a problem with connection
to vCenter: if we consider case with default installation, then vCenter
starts with self-signed certificate which cannot be verified using linux
shipped CA bundle. Glance starts, but fails to do any useful work,
because it generates SSL errors due to inability to verify vCenter
TLS/SSL certificate.

User can provide its own CA bundle file for Glance to verify connection,
but currently puppet-glance does not support this. This patch aims to
fix this problem, it:
- introduces new optional parameter $vcenter_ca_file which undef by
  default, which means that value will not be written to glance-api.conf
- it switches default value of vmware_api_insecure to True
- provides rspec tests for changed behaviour

Change-Id: Icef5c35ad1128df465da548dd880a0dfeeadb5e1
Related-bug: #1559067
'}]
commit_message:
Implement ability to pass CA bundle certificate for vCenter server

Glance with vsphere backend by default verifies vCenter server TLS/SSL
certificate using system truststore (e.g.
/etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt). Here is a problem with connection
to vCenter: if we consider case with default installation, then vCenter
starts with self-signed certificate which cannot be verified using linux
shipped CA bundle. Glance starts, but fails to do any useful work,
because it generates SSL errors due to inability to verify vCenter
TLS/SSL certificate.

User can provide its own CA bundle file for Glance to verify connection,
but currently puppet-glance does not support this. This patch aims to
fix this problem, it:
- introduces new optional parameter $vcenter_ca_file which undef by
  default, which means that value will not be written to glance-api.conf
- it switches default value of vmware_api_insecure to True
- provides rspec tests for changed behaviour

Change-Id: Icef5c35ad1128df465da548dd880a0dfeeadb5e1
Related-bug: #1559067

commit_message:
Fix repository server upgrades

When upgrading the repository server, the pip.conf needs to be absent
for the upgrade to succeed. In order for the playbook to succeed which
performs this action, we need to gather facts for ``ansible_env`` to be
defined and to appropriately use ansible's file module.

Closes-Bug: #1566915
Change-Id: I0e6078adbc3260ea7df816a485b93e606cd5f131

commit_message:
Turn off set -x before running dib in tests

We have set -x on in our parent shell in tests. This causes
disk-image-create to be run wit set -x which explodes our logging
(this includes listing every file in our images).

Change-Id: I949a81dc27564eace47987ff043004a914ed21ff

commit_message:
Always reset-failed ivs before restart ivs

When os-net-config is called too frequent,
ivs may occasionally fail to restart.
This change ensures that reset-failed ivs
is always called before restart ivs, such
that ivs can always successfully be restarted.

Change-Id: I431b2712d73c48bcccdb72dc8075c9d451ac1e95

commit_message:
Proposal of adding sort parameter to list notifications

I'm planning to change pagination style to Horizon standard in monasca-ui.
Horizon standard pagination style will need fewer code than current
implementation and will be easier to maintain.
But this change will need sort parameter to api. Alarm Definitions and
Alarms have already sort_by parameter. So I added sort_by parameter
to Notifications.

Change-Id: Ic7dd98c027476ad19174f52ddd2d4ce6523c50cc

[{'number': 10, 'created': '2016-04-06 03:32:06.000000000', 'files': ['lib/nova'], 'message': 'Remove project_id from nova service urls

Nova API itself supports both URL modes:
  with project-id and without project-id
However, we are changing service catalogs for removing project-id
based on the discussion.
We have agreement on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/181393 like the
following:

 - Standard required naming for endpoints (versioned vs. unversioned,
   contains project ID vs. no project ID).
    * We want unversioned endpoints so that the user can get
      information about multiple available versions in a given cloud.
    * We do not want project ID, account ID, or tenant ID as part of
      the resource URI for an OpenStack API endpoint.

direction.

Change-Id: Ifd74152727b5c0c75924419a7a52e024a69ce72c
'}]
commit_message:
Remove project_id from nova service urls

Nova API itself supports both URL modes:
  with project-id and without project-id
However, we are changing service catalogs for removing project-id
based on the discussion.
We have agreement on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/181393 like the
following:

 - Standard required naming for endpoints (versioned vs. unversioned,
   contains project ID vs. no project ID).
    * We want unversioned endpoints so that the user can get
      information about multiple available versions in a given cloud.
    * We do not want project ID, account ID, or tenant ID as part of
      the resource URI for an OpenStack API endpoint.

So this patch removes project-id from Nova service catalog for this
direction.

Change-Id: Ifd74152727b5c0c75924419a7a52e024a69ce72c

commit_message:
Fix volume retype failure with on-demand policy

After introducing these two fixes, retype with on-demand
policy doesn't change volume type even if the volume
migration is succeeded because swap of volume_type_id
and volume_type are skipped.

https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1547546
https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1555862

We should update of volume_type_id at least so that source
volume can be updated as a new volume type after volume
retype operation.

Change-Id: I28a5d9c88dc5e4ae0b4a7357645d4218b76b17aa
Closes-Bug: #1565133

commit_message:
Add max_retries to nova.conf

nova-conductor retry establish connection mariadb,
after 10 times (default), if mariadb up and running,
it still failed. Need add database.max_retries=-1 in nova.conf,
so nova-conductor tries to connect mariadb infinitely.

Change-Id: Ia0a88336654ff377b9b01abbd693f75223829d74
Closes-Bug: #1505636

commit_message:
Apply host security hardening by default

Security hardening has been applied to all gate jobs since January
2016 in the Mitaka release. This patch enables security hardening
for all deployments in Newton by changing the
apply_security_hardening variable to true by default.

commit_message:
set l2_population to be "true".

This fixes the upgrade issues from  r11.1.3 to 12.0.8
which introduced l2_population by default to false
when the variable is not defined in user_variables
and is undocumented. This causes new virtual machines
on vxlan to be not accessible.

Addresses bug #1563448

Change-Id: Iae3d3dff5e9b20e9c9b0d82159a1b053fc5f004f

commit_message:
Fix up online_data_migrations manage command to be consistent

This adds a consistent return value meaning to the online_data_migrations
command for better behavior in a scripting environment. If migrations
are complete, return 0, else return 1. If there was bad input, then we
return 127. Also consider max=0 to be an error so that we don't act like
migrations are complete if you provide that value.

Change-Id: I7662bad6821863be6f48e55de8483903aa25c491

commit_message:
Log hint when --enable present with --disable-reason

--enable and --disable-reason should be mutually exclusive in "compute
service set" command, but now when they are present at the same time,
--disable-reason would be ignored silently. Fix these and add some hints
about --disable-reason argument is ignored in this situation.

Change-Id: I43254b6bc40fcae4fd0dc3457f26fad84c267072
Closes-Bug: #1556801

commit_message:
Ping retry

The single ping method in the validation script is causing for
deployments to fail. When reviewing the network connectivity, we are
finding we actually do have connectivity
( https://gist.github.com/jtaleric/0276a117625e44993be0 ). This patch is
to change the ping count from 1 to 10, to ensure the network is up.

Closes-Bug: 1563521
Change-Id: I9772407554dffa91978a49a16490ef9ed448a054

commit_message:
The implementation of distributed-DNAT

This patch implements the distributed DNAT of blueprint distributed-fip. The
first stage only implements the tunnel type external network. The change as
below.

1. A df-l3-agent will be used to replace neutron-l3-agent.
df-l3-agent need to be deployed on the centralized network node.
2. A new DNAT app will be loaded to dragonflow controller.
The dnat_app.DNATApp configuration item need to be assigned.

The next stage will support
1. integrate with security group
Current implement will not jump to SG processing due to SG is not ready.

2. vlan network

commit_message:
Add console allowed origins setting

Adds a DEFAULT/console_allowed_origins to the console
websocket proxy to allow connections from other Origin hostnames
(other than only the hostname in the Host header.)

Origin header checking was introduced in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/163033/ as a fix for bug 1409142
and CVE-2015-0259.  However there are valid use cases where you
want to do cross-site web socket connections.

This patch allows for controlled cross-site web socket connections
to the console proxy services.

DocImpact

Change-Id: If7995bb7afc255f5ad834dc8a7044ef38b6cb335
Closes-bug: 1474079

commit_message:
Remove backend interface and common code out of identity.core

This removes dependencies where backend code references code in the
core.  The reasoning being that the core should know about the backend
interface, but the backends should not know anything about the core
(separation of concerns).  And part of the risk here is a potential for
circular dependencies.

- Moved the filter_user method to backends/base.py.  This method is
only used by the backends.

- Moved the interfaces (base) to modules inside the backends. Interfaces
should be closer to the code that implements them and again, wanted to
remove the dependency where the backends were referencing code in the
core.

Partial-Bug: #1563101

Change-Id: I5ff9c4e4b6d64750f5db2a73cc4317358aea0649

commit_message:
Remove flavor seeding from the base migration

In a time long ago and a land far far away, someone thought it was a
good idea to populate the database with default flavors. That was
probably reasonable at the time, but it no longer makes sense and
in fact causes us some pain now.

This patch removes those default flavors from the database. That means
that new deploys will not have them, but doesn't actually rewrite
history in any way.

This will require changes to our docs, which largely assume the presence
of these default flavors from time zero.

DocImpact

Depends-On: Ic275887e97221d9ce5ce6f12cdcfb5ac94e300b0
Change-Id: I80b63ce1ebca01be61ac0f43d26a2992ecf16678

commit_message:
Track the api_interface in the keepalived

The {{ kolla_external_vip_interface }} is added to the
track_interface group when needed. But it is not enough. the
{{ api_interface }} is also required.

when the {{ api_interface }} down, the keepalived should go to FAULT
state.

Closes-Bug: #1565282

commit_message:
Shutdown backend EC connection contexts on disconnect

When eventlet.wsgi closes an ECAppIter on client disconnect we need to
make sure our sub-iterators are also closed.  We already kill the
backend sockets, but the executing contexts are left running until
they timeout.  A slow client can result in needlessly holding queued
backend fragments until the client_timeout (default 60s).

Update associated test that exposed the problem to demonstrate the
issue more quickly.

Change-Id: Ibbc89449e7878fc4215e47e3f7dfe4ae58a2d638

commit_message:
Bypass repo server if missing pip upgrade packages

The function get_pip upgrades the pip packages for pip. If OSA is
updated to require newer versions these may not be present on the repo
server and this will cause bootstrap-ansible.sh to fail.

Update the get_pip function to fallback on calling pip with the
--isolated flag when pip is installed and the pip packages are being
upgraded.

Change-Id: Ifa644b9bf6aa8b20028eb0257c40fe20f3ab1a3b
(cherry picked from commit 721ef48fbf66e375af583710117f5c3bfbace9b9)
(cherry picked from commit 9c0dbd6820f6b907172656a2bad7a0fc1db81043)

commit_message:
Remove deprecated 'verbose' argument

- argument list to abstract methods replaced with '**kwargs'.
- added abstract methods Node.has_snapshot() and Node.get_snapshots()
  for fuel-qa compatibility. It is required for baremetal driver which
  doesn't have snapshots, but fuel-qa code use these methods for all
  nodes.

Change-Id: I0e2d04ee284860b97837297951723c948d8a6fcf
blueprint: template-based-virtual-devops-environments

commit_message:
Use physical host interfaces to connect virtual and baremetal networks

* Two new attributes in the Libvirt driver for L2NetworkDevice:

  - vlan_ifaces = []
    If Libvirt network create a bridge with name virbr1, then some tagged
    interfaces will be created on this bridge: virbr1.100, virbr1.101, ...

    Example: vlan_ifaces = [100, 101, 102]
    $ cat /etc/network/interfaces
    ...
    auto virbr1.100
    iface virbr1.100 inet manual
       vlan_raw_device virbr1
    auto virbr1.101
    iface virbr1.101 inet manual
       vlan_raw_device virbr1
    auto virbr1.102
    iface virbr1.102 inet manual
       vlan_raw_device virbr1

  - parent_iface = {phys_dev=None, l2_net_dev=None, tag=None}
    Should be specified only one device: 'phys_dev' or 'l2_net_dev'.

    If Libvirt network create a bridge with name virbr3, then a parent
    interface can be added to the bridge when the network starts:

    Example: parent_iface = {phys_dev='eth5', l2_net_dev=None, tag=None}
    $ brctl addif virbr3 eth5

    Example: parent_iface = {phys_dev=None, l2_net_dev='admin', tag=100}
    $ brctl addif virbr3 virbr1.100    # 'admin' network created virbr1

* Allow to connect node interfaces to l2_network_device from another
  group (cross-connections)

Co-Authored-By: Dmitry Tyzhnenko <dtyzhnenko@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: I9b78c6d4c77438241315c4ea60dae44ea975fb5c

To send the Inspector ramdisk over HTTP rather than TFTP, we must first
send an iPXE boot image that knows how to speak HTTP, and then instruct
it to "chainload" the inspector ramdisk. Previously, we could only do
this if the machine being introspected had BIOS firmware. However, most
modern servers now use UEFI firmware, which requires a different iPXE
boot image (as described at http://ipxe.org/howto/chainloading).

problem described at http://forum.ipxe.org/showthread.php?tid=7589.

 - downloading the images from ipxe.org would make our users vulnerable

commit_message:
Allow chainloading of Inspector ramdisk over UEFI

To send the Inspector ramdisk over HTTP rather than TFTP, we must first
send an iPXE boot image that knows how to speak HTTP, and then instruct
it to "chainload" the inspector ramdisk. Previously, we could only do
this if the machine being introspected had BIOS firmware. However, most
modern servers now use UEFI firmware, which requires a different iPXE
boot image (as described at http://ipxe.org/howto/chainloading).

We must specify the initrd in the iPXE `kernel` line to avoid the
problem described at http://forum.ipxe.org/showthread.php?tid=7589.

We include the iPXE binary images directly in the files/ subdirectory
and serve them from the puppet master. This is because

 - while there is a Debian package that contains both images, there is
   currently no package for Red Hat systems that contains the UEFI
   image;
 - downloading the images from ipxe.org would make our users vulnerable
   to any attack affecting that site.

Change-Id: I1f08578d4005c33feed84d4783a7a7693d13920c
Depends-On: I7dc191a38132db5fc2c68846c036d5b45061b398

commit_message:
Set 0644 file mode for volume content files

We need read rights for everyone to make regular user possible to
export system test environments without superuser privileges.
Also it helps to save time when older version of libvirt with poor
vol-download performance is used.

Author: Aliaksei Cherniakou

Change-Id: I18a973daf8d7b7ae5890100878df0d94635a6241

commit_message:
Add ip_reserved and ip_ranges attributes to AddressPool

- ip_reserved is for store reserved IPs, such as:
  - 'gateway' IP of the network,
  - 'l2_network_device' IP of the libvirt network
    (which can be different from the gateway), etc.

- ip_ranges is for store IP ranges in the network, such as:
  - 'default' for common IP ranges,
  - 'floating' for floating IP range of public network,
  - 'dhcp' for libvirt's DHCP range, etc.

- add node.networkconfig property to easy get NetworkConfig
  objects.

blueprint: template-based-virtual-devops-environments
Change-Id: I018f0a7b11b5254565e693ff8009b07de120c59e

commit_message:
libvirt: return a root block device

Moves find_disk to Guest's object and adds method to retrieve root
block device according virt_type + Enhances BlocDevice object to get
disk format.

Implements: blueprint libvirt-clean-driver
Change-Id: Id388e98e58e6f1d420629ec1ff9e4b22d2717960

commit_message:
Enable download of tinyipa prebuilt image

Now there is a post job to build tinyipa and publish it to
tarballs.openstack.org, we can start to use it in the ironic devstack
script to prevent the need to build the image every time.

Change-Id: I641a5afe8318ec0848395b2b70e056c448f3dd00

commit_message:
Add fullstack cross-process port/ip address fixtures

We've had a series of bugs with resources that need
to be unique on the system across test runner
processes. Ports are used by neutron-server and the
OVS agent when run in native openflow mode. The function
that generates ports looks up random unused ports and
starts the service. However, it is raceful: By the time the
port is found to be unused and the service is started,
another test runner can pick the same random port.
With close to 65536 ports to choose from, the chance
for collision is low, but given enough test runs, it's
happened a non-trivial amount of times, and given that
a voting job needs a very low false-negative rate, we
need a more robust solution. The same applies to IP
addresses that are used by the OVS agent in tunneling
mode, and for the LB agent in all modes. With IP addresses,
we don't check if the IP address is used, we simply
pick a random address from a large pool, and again
we've seen a non-trivial amount of test failures.

The bugs referenced below had simple, short term solutions
applied but the bugs remain remain. This patch is a correct,
long term solution that doesn't rely on chance.

This patch adds a resource allocator that uses the disk
to persist allocations. Access to the disk is guarded
via a file lock. IP address, networks and ports fixtures
use an allocator internally.

Closes-Bug: #1551288
Closes-Bug: #1561248
Closes-Bug: #1560277
Change-Id: I46c0ca138b806759128462f8d44a5fab96a106d3

commit_message:
Added precheck to check kernel version 4.2 on Ubuntu 14.04.

Kolla recommends LTS wily kernel version 4.2 on Ubuntu 14.04.

http://docs.openstack.org/developer/kolla/quickstart.html#installing-dependencies

The precheck check the running kernel version, because checking
the linux-image-generic-lts-wily cannot be a valid check.

The package (linux-image-generic-lts-wily) can be installed, but
the running kernel can be other version.

Closes-Bug: #1563500
Co-Authored-By: Vikram Hosakote <vhosakot@cisco.com>
Change-Id: I4e08bca95493b2dbd0ad5f8d1ea4e07b18c4959d
(cherry picked from commit 833c1269c7941498787d49ce879be6c283728407)

commit_message:
Resolve compatibility with Keystone 8.1.0

Keystone released a Liberty series point release as 8.1.0; the
existing Liberty version match was for 8.0.*; resync stable
charm-helpers to pickup inclusion of 8.1.* as a Liberty release.

I've also included the setup work for stable branch in this
change.

Change-Id: I1f0cd2b0fc05cf9903346b55fc78d3a04153ab5a

commit_message:
puppet-prepare-node after bindep for puppet jobs

We need to ensure bindep runs first before the removal of packages.
This will avoid breakages of removing a repository that bindep depends
on.

Change-Id: I3cb403ab6f6e83dce39b8a5e376bbcb4b2f8b309

If protocol was present in the dict, but was None, then it was never
re-instantiated after being popped out of the dict. This later resulted

Change-Id: I4985e7b54117bee3241d7365cb438197a09b9b86

commit_message:
Don't drop 'protocol' from client supplied security_group_rule dict

If protocol was present in the dict, but was None, then it was never
re-instantiated after being popped out of the dict. This later resulted
in KeyError when trying to access the key on the dict.

Change-Id: I4985e7b54117bee3241d7365cb438197a09b9b86
Closes-Bug: #1566327
(cherry picked from commit 5a41caa47a080fdbc1801e2771163734b9790c57)

commit_message:
Restructure resource backend

- Rename core.py to managers.py, since it owns Manager classes,
  similarly to controllers.py, which owns Controller classes;
- Extract the abstract drivers from managers.py and put them in their
  own file called drivers.py.

Change-Id: Ifc4a5800cfcd0be006325b2321ef577bc148a8da

commit_message:
Update HPE 3PAR devref docs

With the Mitaka release multiple changes have been made to the
Manila driver:
    - Access rules changes for both NFS and CIFS shares.
    - IP and user access rules changes for both NFS and CIFS shares.
    - Client version bump.
    - Deleting of file tree for nested shares.

Change-Id: I09fbaad15e18c5babdbe8a419737ffc7b23d0d7d

commit_message:
objects: Add 2 relation fields to PciDevice

We will need to access this information on object instances in order to
fix bug 1565785, since we can't access it by querying the DB.

This patch adds the objects fields to hold the needed information.

Follow up patches will make sure it's populated and used when needed.

commit_message:
Node model changes

Node extensions:
    Role field of Node model now controlls which extension class should
    be used for a certain node. It allows to get additional method for
    'Node' object that are depended on the node role.
    It allows to put spesific methods for Fuel master node in a separate
    class, such as bootstrap the master node; add a non-Fuel nodes to
    extend environment functionality (pre-deployed nodes with customer's
    operation system; OVS nodes; etc)

Change-Id: Ieb6ec87d61ba68b862c350342eef081e70adf028
blueprint: template-based-virtual-devops-environments

commit_message:
New Network Models

    AddressPool - stores IP pools used in the environment. These pools
                  can be assigned to l2 network devices (with the model
                  L2NetworkDevice) and/or to different OpenStack networks
                  (with the model NetworkPool).
    L2NetworkDevice - stores information about l2 network devices
                      defined within a certain group and bind to
                      address pool. For libvirt driver it describes
                      bridges, for baremetal driver - network devices.
    NetworkPool - bind the specific address pool for use with
                  a specific OpenStack network.
    NetworkConfig - bind a Node interface to a list of OpenStack network
                    that are supposed to be assigned to the interface.
                    If a bonding was configured from a hardware side,
                    then bonding interface can be described here.

'Network' model was replaced by two new models: L2NetworkDevice and
AddressPool.

'DiskDevice' was moved to devops/volume.py

Change-Id: Icd2d63a6170aa3255ce3df1eb3cecf3b87cf8cd0
blueprint: template-based-virtual-devops-environments

commit_message:
ParamedModel - Parameterizable model class

This patch adds a class which allows all derived classes to be
polymorphically extended by extra fields. All additional fields
will be saved as a json in a special db field called 'params'.

It also allows:
 - to save/load derived classes to the same parent table.
 - filter by new fields.
 - to store nested fields.

Change-Id: I2b2024eec126fd9c05a36247c87592d481530104
blueprint: template-based-virtual-devops-environments

commit_message:
WIP Return port_id in the addresses structure

This is an initial POC to point to whie writing a spec. The goal here
is to return a port_id for fixed ip addresses in a neutron deployment
so that the end user does not have to follow a server create call with
a neutron port list call to find the port id to use during a floating
IP create call - since nova already has this information in its data
structures.

Change-Id: I0e7b991e09a974369fef6ee7d79d4800a5fc8640

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-05 21:34:14.000000000', 'files': ['novaclient/tests/unit/v2/contrib/test_baremetal.py', 'novaclient/v2/contrib/baremetal.py'], 'message': "Remove busted baremetal CLIs and API bindings

The os-baremetal-nodes compute API does not proxy
baremetal node create/delete or interface add/remove
requests to Ironic, so there is no point in even
having CLIs or python bindings for these operations
in the client.

There isn't a point in deprecating these since they

Change-Id: Id5dd7fbddff87e506460904e352713ae777a8073
Closes-Bug: #1566535
"}]
commit_message:
Remove busted baremetal CLIs and API bindings

The os-baremetal-nodes compute API does not proxy
baremetal node create/delete or interface add/remove
requests to Ironic, so there is no point in even
having CLIs or python bindings for these operations
in the client.

There isn't a point in deprecating these since they
are already unusable, so let's just remove them.

Change-Id: Id5dd7fbddff87e506460904e352713ae777a8073
Closes-Bug: #1566535

commit_message:
[Reports] Show task uuid or task results file name in report

This patch shows task uuid or file name in HTML report:
  * page with benchmark results - under benchmark header
  * on overview page - as pop-up title for each benchmark

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-01 08:42:09.000000000', 'files': ['elements/undercloud-install/pre-install.d/01-persistent-journal'], 'message': 'Temporarily set +e on systemd-journald restart for +bug/1564471

Though the restart of the systemd-journald service succeeds fine, an
assertion error during the restart of the systemd-journald service
causes the instack-undercloud install to fail (this is during an
undercloud upgrade in fact, details in the bug).

This review sets +e to allow the script to continue and then also

commit_message:
Temporarily set +e on systemd-journald restart for +bug/1564471

Though the restart of the systemd-journald service succeeds fine, an
assertion error during the restart of the systemd-journald service
causes the instack-undercloud install to fail (this is during an
undercloud upgrade in fact, details in the bug).

This review sets +e to allow the script to continue and then also
checks that the service was indeed started OK, exiting otherwise.

Related-Bug: 1564471
Change-Id: I38c14a6b143b51dec6f6f88f2e1cb591e07a08b3
(cherry picked from commit cc41b7a1f9009a1dd24193b3a7e98a13496cbcc0)

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-05 16:04:11.000000000', 'files': ['openstackclient/tests/test_shell.py'], 'message': 'Use fixtures and addCleanup instead of tearDown

Nothing ensures tearDown call as tearDown is called only if test
succeeds. This change replaces tearDown use with:

* addCleanup use to stop mocks
* EnvFixture which ensures to unmock environment thanks to useFixture.

Change-Id: I1ff422e6a7585bc48b04b8f5c4cc1e7e9ddab1bc
'}]
commit_message:
Use fixtures and addCleanup instead of tearDown

Nothing ensures tearDown call as tearDown is called only if test
succeeds. This change replaces tearDown use with:

* addCleanup use to stop mocks
* EnvFixture which ensures to unmock environment thanks to useFixture.

Change-Id: I1ff422e6a7585bc48b04b8f5c4cc1e7e9ddab1bc

commit_message:
libvirt: prevent serial console port exhaustion

When an instance gets rebuild, new serial console ports will be
created although they could be reused. This leads to a port exhaustion.

This patch reuses the once created ports in case the instance already
exists. This is also important when doing a live migration because
that code path calls "_get_guest_config()" multiple times.

Related-Bug: 1455252
Closes-Bug: 1489853
Co-Authored-By: Marco Pavone <marco.pavone@de.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I6d8f8542e517cd1e7d2ed1c2bbf7bcf16505127c

commit_message:
fix resource_type table migration

we're incorrectly setting the value of tablename to 'name' rather
than the actually name of resource type. this corrects that.

additional fixes:
- fix incorrect setting nullable=False when it's created as True
initially
- fix incorrect revision string in create_resource_type

Change-Id: Id77239c0e22ac069ebb87fc926a8daaf71ad8177
Closes-Bug: #1565781

commit_message:
Fix invalid error message of volume create

When create a volume with image name, the error message return to
user is invalid if there are several image share the same name.
This change provides a more user-friendly message.

commit_message:
Set rings rx/tx to maximum that supports hardware

All recent versions of the chipset have 4096, but the driver doesn't
autodetect this. Increasing the number of descriptors can improve
performance dramatically on some hosts.

This is also the case with Intel 10GE NICs - the driver defaults to 256
descriptors each for Rx and Tx, even if the hardware supports 4096.

Depends-On: Ib70ae937165ddb2968c9e4346434f18778b31714
Change-Id: I1e5029e793399ff42002f3d203c6ae3bd2608be2
Closes-Bug: #1456723

commit_message:
Refactor driver's listener interface

Current Listener interface has poll() method which return messages

To use it we need have poller thread which is located in MessageHandlerServer
But my investigations of existing driver's code shows that some implemetations have
its own thread inside for processing connection event loop. This event loop received
messages and store in queue object. And then our poller's thread reads this queue
This situation can be improved. we can remove poller's thread, remove queue object
and just call on_message server's callback from connection eventloop thread

This path provide posibility to do this for one of drivers and leave as is other drivers

Change-Id: I3e3d4369d8fdadcecf079d10af58b1e4f5616047

commit_message:
Log warning message if get_subnet_for_dvr fails

When subnet or gateway port has been deleted concurrently, rpc call
to get_subnet_for_dvr will return an empty dict without any value.
ovs_dvr_neutron_agent should be more gracefull and at least log
warning message in that situation.

Change the existing error log to warning, because it is not a server
error, but a fact that should be noticed.

Change-Id: Icb3a57553a8b0eb635c0d85e2c60e7ce519893f6
Closes-bug: #1454921

commit_message:
Add verification for latest apps section

When switching projects(tenants) the latest apps did not check whether
the application package is available for deployment in current tenant.
This change adds such check to avoid situations, when a user would
attempt to add an app to environment, that is not available in his
project/tenant.

Change-Id: I9f9c14827932d8187e5815fbbd2f22b1a6801ce8
Closes-Bug: #1558329

When protocol is ICMP in security group, port_range_min and
port_range_max are used to indicate type and code for ICMP. The

commit_message:
Fix incorrect ICMP rule in SecurityGroup

When protocol is ICMP in security group, port_range_min and
port_range_max are used to indicate type and code for ICMP. The
default port setting in core library generates ICMP rule with
incorrect setting 'icmptype 0 code 0', which make user cannot ping
instance created by Murano environment. So removed them.

Change-Id: I93b5073db2ece804e3eccdde8432216d4fb12301
Closes-Bug: #1512710

commit_message:
Support using internal network for clients

Openstack mostly defaults to using public endpoints for
internal communication between services. This patch adds
a new option use-internal-endpoints which, if set to True,
will configure services to use internal endpoints where
possible.

Closes-Bug: 1456876
Change-Id: Iadd1e4e8833f637d75d3b5080e49ddabb0f78427

This might prevent dropping members from corosync cluster on high load
environments. Symptoms of this problem happening can sometimes be found
in corosync log:

dub 05 17:23:45 overcloud-controller-0 corosync[14152]: [MAIN ] Corosync
main process was not scheduled for 3691.8391 ms (threshold is 1320.0000
ms). Consider token timeout increase.

The default in the Puppet manifest is 1 second, which matches the

Change-Id: I5ea850ada657e5eecafa3e8b28613a0ac48e78f3
'}]
commit_message:
Increase corosync token timeout

This might prevent dropping members from corosync cluster on high load
environments. Symptoms of this problem happening can sometimes be found
in corosync log:

dub 05 17:23:45 overcloud-controller-0 corosync[14152]: [MAIN ] Corosync
main process was not scheduled for 3691.8391 ms (threshold is 1320.0000
ms). Consider token timeout increase.

The default in the Puppet manifest is 1 second, which matches the
corosync default, and we override it with hiera to 10 seconds.

Change-Id: I5ea850ada657e5eecafa3e8b28613a0ac48e78f3

While working on I62bc11887283201be0bcdcfe9fa58b3f6156c754 a
problem with the flavor migration functional tests was discovered.
Due to a faulty test setup where db's aren't set up correctly,
those tests fail to test the intended behavior.

commit_message:
Fix flavor migration tests and edge case found

While working on I62bc11887283201be0bcdcfe9fa58b3f6156c754 a
problem with the flavor migration functional tests was discovered.
Due to a faulty test setup where db's aren't set up correctly,
those tests fail to test the intended behavior.

By fixing this, an edge case was discovered where if no previous
flavors exists during a reset of the autoincrementing flavor id,
the query to get the current max id returns None and not an int.

Change-Id: I627a8a38449ab48349c91d5be05bf8baeb525fab

commit_message:
Fix empty Create/Update column in cluster/profile... tables

we use the filter parse_isotime
(https://github.com/openstack/horizon/blob/master/horizon/utils/filters.py#L32),
the function except string rather than datetime object.

But the python-openstack
(https://github.com/openstack/python-openstacksdk/blob/master/openstack/cluster/v1/profile.py#L44)
return datetime object parsed from ISO 8601 formatted string,
so we could remove the filter.

Change-Id: I55832284ef8716e7ea8f17ec34edc9ef9f5d02b7
Closes-Bug: #1566349

This reverts commit c0d53a3d899afafd34243fc8804f098e227d5592.

This patch broke rule creation due to validation code messing with user
passed dict. Let's revert in Liberty until a proper fix lands master.

Related-Bug: #1566327

commit_message:
Switch to 2.1 default api_version in v2.Client

Direct initialization of versioned clients is restricted, but we tries to
decrease the number of possible bugs and issues, so default value for
api_version was added to v2.Client .

Let's set it to 2.1, since 2.0 is too old API version.

Change-Id: If127f858f7f670a090a57267f46a69ea4c056cce

commit_message:
OVS: Add mac spoofing filtering to flows

The mac-spoofing filtering done by iptables was
not adequate. See the bug report and change
I39dc0e23fc118ede19ef2d986b29fc5a8e48ff78 for
more information.

This patch adds flows to the OVS agent to block
any traffic from the VM that isn't in the allowed
address pairs macs or the mac address field of
the port.

Closes-Bug: #1558658
Change-Id: I02984b21872e0f183db7404c10d8180dbd89075f

deprecated in favor of 'topics' for oslo.messaging Notifiers. This
updates the Nova usage in order to not get yelled at.

commit_message:
[Manila] Add grenade job

To be able to test Manila upgrades 'grenade' job is required.
Add such for Manila project to experimental pipeline.
Make it non-voting until it becomes stable.

Change-Id: I550bcaadacd811464997be7806c9b8d94799e38c

commit_message:
Fix case-sensitive filter value in cfapi

String values for filters in glare case-sensitive unlike murano db-api.
This patch for cfapi fix services retrieve from glare api.

Change-Id: Id9d0209ecd259162cabb9694a85b48612501a142

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-01 08:48:03.000000000', 'files': ['elements/undercloud-install/pre-install.d/01-persistent-journal'], 'message': 'Temporarily set +e on systemd-journald restart for +bug/1564471

Though the restart of the systemd-journald service succeeds fine, an
assertion error during the restart of the systemd-journald service
causes the instack-undercloud install to fail (this is during an
undercloud upgrade in fact, details in the bug).

This review sets +e to allow the script to continue and then also

'}]
commit_message:
Temporarily set +e on systemd-journald restart for +bug/1564471

Though the restart of the systemd-journald service succeeds fine, an
assertion error during the restart of the systemd-journald service
causes the instack-undercloud install to fail (this is during an
undercloud upgrade in fact, details in the bug).

This review sets +e to allow the script to continue and then also
checks that the service was indeed started OK, exiting otherwise.

Related-Bug: 1564471
Change-Id: I38c14a6b143b51dec6f6f88f2e1cb591e07a08b3
(cherry picked from commit cc41b7a1f9009a1dd24193b3a7e98a13496cbcc0)

commit_message:
Add tests for new data-driven upgrade procedure

The upgrade procedure was completely changed because
of changing base OS for Fuel (Centos7). It leads to
complete refactoring of all upgrade-related code
including tests

This commit should be backportable to 7.0 branch
because we need to prepare some 7.0 clusters.
This is the reason of rejecting SSHManager
 _for this commit_. It will be integrated later.

Change-Id: I1932c28beb9a7101019a02d4cd5245a1a0996a05
Partial-bug:1546943
(cherry picked from commit 8b9bac01e99effac364491ba9f12e0f2f17b91ea)

commit_message:
Add tests for new data-driven upgrade procedure

The upgrade procedure was completely changed because
of changing base OS for Fuel (Centos7). It leads to
complete refactoring of all upgrade-related code
including tests

This commit should be backportable to 7.0 branch
because we need to prepare some 7.0 clusters.
This is the reason of rejecting SSHManager
 _for this commit_. It will be integrated later.

Change-Id: I1932c28beb9a7101019a02d4cd5245a1a0996a05
Partial-bug:1546943

commit_message:
[admin-guide] Fix IPs in Share Replication documentation

The IP Addresses used in the documentation of the replication
feature recently introduced in Shared File Systems service could
be perceived to be mis-configuration.

Replace them with randomly generated private IPs and clarify
the usage of these IPs.

Also separate the 'access rules' and 'snapshots' sections
for better readability.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I00b7df8472950a18f28dda5bacf23265b17047d7

subject: Bypass repo server if missing pip upgrade packages
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-03-08 12:24:22.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/scripts-library.sh'], 'message': 'Bypass repo server if missing pip upgrade packages

The function get_pip upgrades the pip packages for pip. If OSA is
updated to require newer versions these may not be present on the repo
server and this will cause bootstrap-ansible.sh to fail.

Update the get_pip function to fallback on calling pip with the
--isolated flag when pip is installed and the pip packages are being
upgraded.

Change-Id: Ifa644b9bf6aa8b20028eb0257c40fe20f3ab1a3b
(cherry picked from commit 721ef48fbf66e375af583710117f5c3bfbace9b9)
'}]
commit_message:
Bypass repo server if missing pip upgrade packages

The function get_pip upgrades the pip packages for pip. If OSA is
updated to require newer versions these may not be present on the repo
server and this will cause bootstrap-ansible.sh to fail.

Update the get_pip function to fallback on calling pip with the
--isolated flag when pip is installed and the pip packages are being
upgraded.

Change-Id: Ifa644b9bf6aa8b20028eb0257c40fe20f3ab1a3b
(cherry picked from commit 721ef48fbf66e375af583710117f5c3bfbace9b9)

commit_message:
Use global_physnet_mtu to fix MTU settings in Mitaka

[DEFAULT]/network_device_mtu option is deprecated and will be removed
in Newton. However, new [ml2]/segment_mtu is deprecated too according to
neutron/common/config.py. This patch replaces network_device_mtu with
new [DEFAULT]/global_physnet_mtu.

Change-Id: I9eb5df274e5d7f1f89c5f894526d07d20d4cd794
Closes-bug: #1565036
(cherry picked from commit d301833c2c379db706a52a582f502bb14cd4d34f)

subject: Tune interval for node provision state check
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-03-31 15:59:07.000000000', 'files': ['ironic_tempest_plugin/tests/scenario/baremetal_manager.py'], 'message': 'Tune interval for node provision state check

By default node_provision_state is checked each 1 second.
It may cause test to fail while actual test result is success due to
testr bug #1382579
Also it creates additional load on service and increase execution
time for test.
This patch set interval to 30 sec.
It should speed up the test on overloaded nodes.

Related-Bug: #1382579
Change-Id: I631b0ee5fd8ff7c1d655b52496cf920d088c253d
'}]
commit_message:
Tune interval for node provision state check

By default node_provision_state is checked each 1 second.
It may cause test to fail while actual test result is success due to
testr bug #1382579
Also it creates additional load on service and increase execution
time for test.
This patch set interval to 30 sec.
It should speed up the test on overloaded nodes.

Related-Bug: #1382579
Change-Id: I631b0ee5fd8ff7c1d655b52496cf920d088c253d

commit_message:
Memory consumption reduced in fuel-stats analytics

We had huge memory consumption on fetching OSWLs due to fetching
clusters data in each OSWL row.

Joined clusters data removed from each OSWL row. Explicit
fetching of version info from clusters is introduced to CSV
exporter.

We are using SQLAlchemy yield_per for fetching large query results.
Yeld_per page parameter reduced from 1000 to 100.

We still have issues with memory consumption in all
reports generation. Thus we are temporary removing link
on 'All reports' from web UI.

Example uWSGI configuration changed to start http service.

Change-Id: I66c97058c0f15f8a15b626ab1fa222106754a455
Partial-Bug: #1564427

commit_message:
ODL v2: Fix multiple updates race

In case there are multiple updates in the journal there is a chance that
the updates will be sent to ODL controller in the wrong order.
The fix verifies that if there are multiple updates on the same object
only the last update will be sent to the ODL controller and all
other updates (journal rows) will be set to 'failed'.

Change-Id: I44d0de7d3ab8f385ef5dccaaeb2348e830a83304
Closes-Bug: #1561516

commit_message:
Add tests for new data-driven upgrade procedure

The upgrade procedure was completely changed because
of changing base OS for Fuel (Centos7). It leads to
complete refactoring of all upgrade-related code
including tests

This commit should be backportable to 7.0 branch
because we need to prepare some 7.0 clusters.
This is the reason of rejecting SSHManager
 _for this commit_. It will be integrated later.

commit_message:
Add MASTER=bond SLAVE=yes to linux bond interfaces

When configuring a linux bond with interfaces we have a bug
(due to a missing unit test) where the interfaces weren't
being configured with MASTER=<bond_name> SLAVE=yes. This
patch adds a unit test to check for the required configuration
and cleans up the logic in impl_ifcfg.py to handle it correctly
by simply checking for the linux_bond_name property which
is already set for us via objects.py.

See also: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1323717

Change-Id: Ic632c52265dcbbe6c0ace782e633a2030ad25e6f
Closes-bug: 1566428

commit_message:
cephfs_native: Change backend snapshot dir's name

A snapshot of a share created by cephfs_native driver can be read from
its corresponding snapshot directory created within the share. The
snapshot directory was named using the snapshot instance ID, which
would be visible only to manila admins. In effect, a non-admin manila
user could not identify the snapshot directory (in the mounted share)
from where he could read the snapshot's contents.

Fix by creating ceph snapshot directories with names that also contain
snapshot IDs that are visible to all users.

Change-Id: Ifda0300c60fca87a3f993c1f2eaeb05d1dd909d4
Closes-Bug: #1563198

commit_message:
L3 agent: match format used by iptables

This fixes the iptables rules generated by the L3 agent
(SNAT, DNAT, set-mark and metadata), and the DHCP agent
(checksum-fill) to match the format that will be returned
by iptables-save to prevent excessive extra replacement
work done by the iptables manager.

It also fixes the iptables test that was not passing the
expected arguments (-p PROTO -m PROTO) for block rules.

A simple test was added to the L3 agent to ensure that the
rules have converged during the normal lifecycle tests.

Closes-Bug: #1566007
Change-Id: I5e8e27cdbf0d0448011881614671efe53bb1b6a1

commit_message:
ovo: Make return values from objects db api consistent

Previously in db api, we returned dictionaries from create() and update()
methods while get() methods returned db models. This patch makes the
return values consistent and thus we always get db model from db api
operations.

Related-Bug: 1541928
Change-Id: I7e9ec4efa20e3d09e1d5a0ca04799095b6ea42b7

subject: Remove ssh host keys when using simple init
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-04-06 05:47:49.000000000', 'files': ['elements/simple-init/cleanup.d/90-remove-ssh-host-keys'], 'message': "Remove ssh host keys when using simple init

In order for glean to operate properly and regenerate ssh host keys it
needs to start on a host without any ssh host keys. We hadn't been doing
this meaning that new host keys were not generated on images using
simple-init. Fix this by having simple-init delete any host keys found
in /etc/ssh late in the build process.

This should force glean/sshd to generate new host keys on first boot
depending on the distro.

Change-Id: Ic917387d92febf21c2cc37dfc1fa83fcf0c8e469
"}]
commit_message:
Remove ssh host keys when using simple init

In order for glean to operate properly and regenerate ssh host keys it
needs to start on a host without any ssh host keys. We hadn't been doing
this meaning that new host keys were not generated on images using
simple-init. Fix this by having simple-init delete any host keys found
in /etc/ssh late in the build process.

This should force glean/sshd to generate new host keys on first boot
depending on the distro.

Change-Id: Ic917387d92febf21c2cc37dfc1fa83fcf0c8e469

subject: Fix timeout on crm_resource --wait
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 1926, 'name': 'Derek Higgins', 'email': 'derekh@redhat.com', 'username': 'derekh'}, {'_account_id': 6796, 'name': 'Giulio Fidente', 'email': 'gfidente@redhat.com', 'username': 'gfidente'}, {'_account_id': 10873, 'name': 'Juan Antonio Osorio Robles', 'email': 'jaosorior@redhat.com', 'username': 'ejuaoso'}, {'_account_id': 12715, 'name': 'John Trowbridge', 'email': 'trown@redhat.com', 'username': 'trown'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-05 12:43:30.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/deploy.sh'], 'message': 'Fix timeout on crm_resource --wait

The wait_for helper is intended for polling. It cannot do timeboxing of
crm_resource --wait, which is a blocking call, e.g. see this snippet
from CI output where it waited 28 minutes (instead of intended 3) before
getting killed by the outer "master" timeout:

2016-04-05 09:35:05.916 | + tripleo wait_for -w 180 --delay 1 -- ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null -o LogLevel=Verbose -o PasswordAuthentication=no -o ConnectionAttempts=32 heat-admin@192.0.2.8 sudo crm_resource -r openstack-heat-api --wait
2016-04-05 10:02:09.019 | /home/jenkins/workspace/gate-tripleo-ci-f22-ha/devstack-gate/functions.sh: line 1148: 16061 Killed                  timeout -s 9 ${REMAINING_TIME}m bash -c "source $WORKSPACE/devstack-gate/functions.sh && $cmd"

Using timeout instead of wait_for should fix this, as it's intended for
blocking calls.

Change-Id: I5eaca1ab3407b42b25d18f11cc7a8a301f56d5f7
'}]
commit_message:
Fix timeout on crm_resource --wait

The wait_for helper is intended for polling. It cannot do timeboxing of
crm_resource --wait, which is a blocking call, e.g. see this snippet
from CI output where it waited 28 minutes (instead of intended 3) before
getting killed by the outer "master" timeout:

2016-04-05 09:35:05.916 | + tripleo wait_for -w 180 --delay 1 -- ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o UserKnownHostsFile=/dev/null -o LogLevel=Verbose -o PasswordAuthentication=no -o ConnectionAttempts=32 heat-admin@192.0.2.8 sudo crm_resource -r openstack-heat-api --wait
2016-04-05 10:02:09.019 | /home/jenkins/workspace/gate-tripleo-ci-f22-ha/devstack-gate/functions.sh: line 1148: 16061 Killed                  timeout -s 9 ${REMAINING_TIME}m bash -c "source $WORKSPACE/devstack-gate/functions.sh && $cmd"

Using timeout instead of wait_for should fix this, as it's intended for
blocking calls.

Change-Id: I5eaca1ab3407b42b25d18f11cc7a8a301f56d5f7

commit_message:
Fix db purge type validation

Moved validation for age_in_days and max_rows from
glance.db.sqlalchemy.api to glance.cmd.manage since
code from purge_deleted_rows() method of
glance.db.sqlalchemy.api is unreachable as it is
throwing ValueError exception for invalid input from
glance.cmd.manage itself.

Related-Bug: #1543937
Change-Id: I4e976fde2a78fd901c233966adc350a0ded41841

commit_message:
IP v6 support coverage in Smoke

This functionality is available since FUEL 8.0
 and should be checked at Smoke group.
  Main part of scenario is the same, as "connectivity from instance...",
  except start of 2 instances in 2 separate networks and
  connectivity check between it using ping6 command.
  IPv6 addresses is stored in log.
  CIDR could be overriden via parameters.

Closes-bug: #1518979

Change-Id: I4699f415785c22fafe2717a35152cab46db7a7b4

commit_message:
Log the SHA of the Git ref for source builds

When using named refs in source builds, e.g. "reference = master", one
can't easily tell from the build output what SHA master actually pointed
to at that point and time. Update the debug output to include this.

Closes-Bug: #1566316

(cherry picked from commit cfd806aeff30818d2c1a909780f141ae0ac8dfef)

Change-Id: Ia228f9845f966b50442cc96e3ab150d3dc97f5f8

commit_message:
WIP: ironic driver: add console-related methods

This patch adds 2 methods below:

- get_serial_console(self, context, instance):
  Aquires serial console information.

- get_console_output(self, context, instance):
  Aquire the content of a console log.

NOTE: This is a proof-of-concept; unit tests will be added later.

Related-Bug: #1526368,#1553083
Change-Id: Ib4bf9127264bba53bc411207ec40444500ed9ef9

commit_message:
Fix fuel master node migration test

- Move assigned_slaves attribute from class scope of BaseActions
class to instance scope of ActionTest class. This is to have this
attribute reset before each template based test of the same run
(otherwise it brings slave info from the 1st test to 2nd and so on).
- Add waiting for cluster nodes to be online after migration.

Change-Id: Iafa38f0f3cfdaa04551ffbcdf6bdfacbdd0abedb
Partial-Bug: #1559050

commit_message:
Fix linting errors in YAML

This change corrects many problems detected by the `yamllint` linter.
It's a preparation for enabling this linter in change
Ie746230f28fe3ed0cf218201d5a3810f7bc44070.

For instance, the first run of the YAML linter helped discovering a key
duplication problem in `oso_ha.yaml`: the `depends_on` key was present
twice, so the first occurence was ignored.

Other changes are cosmetic: extra spaces, extra blank lines, missing
newlines at end-of-file, etc.

Change-Id: I7f2369adfb152fd2a74b9b105e969e653e592922

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-06 06:04:44.000000000', 'files': ['senlin/engine/event.py'], 'message': "Fix event generation

This patch is about a serious bug in event generation. When passing in
an action object, we have been mistakenly using the action.id as the
obj_id. This is leading to the event generated cannot be filtered using
obj_id.

We don't have unit tests for the event module yet. That will be left in
a separate patch.

Change-Id: I542b55871845956c489b1832802bdc80deac210b
Closes-Bug: 1564936
(cherry picked from commit c153bc4e5305ac113136f5125b1a338f1df0591e)
"}]
commit_message:
Fix event generation

This patch is about a serious bug in event generation. When passing in
an action object, we have been mistakenly using the action.id as the
obj_id. This is leading to the event generated cannot be filtered using
obj_id.

We don't have unit tests for the event module yet. That will be left in
a separate patch.

Change-Id: I542b55871845956c489b1832802bdc80deac210b
Closes-Bug: 1564936
(cherry picked from commit c153bc4e5305ac113136f5125b1a338f1df0591e)

commit_message:
Add post job for building and uploading tinyipa

Ironic currently automatically builds and uploads a coreos based IPA
image so that CI jobs don't have to build it every time and so that
people wanting to use Ironic don't have to always build their own. This
patch adds a job to also build the tinyipa version of IPA, so that we
can get the same optimisations.

Depends-On: I9d879689c8e88768aaa96d0033b62d062f9cdc27
Change-Id: I56688bbb3efd5b5a0a14570f4b9733a76d31b71b

Backups now are executed in multithreading.
In case one block fail to be uploaded to swift,
the operation is attempted backup_swift_retry_attempts
conf parameter times.

Added new configuration option backup_swift_threads integer value,

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ica83ab955bf7db8066207bdd9bb0d6f921033254
'}]
commit_message:
Added multithreading support to swift driver for backups.

Backups now are executed in multithreading.
In case one block fail to be uploaded to swift,
the operation is attempted backup_swift_retry_attempts
conf parameter times.

Added new configuration option backup_swift_threads integer value,
default to 4 and capped at SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ica83ab955bf7db8066207bdd9bb0d6f921033254

subject: WIP:make sure conf is loaded first than "@periodics.periodic()"
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2016-03-31 07:32:27.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/cmd/__init__.py', 'ironic/common/service.py', 'ironic/api/app.wsgi', 'ironic/common/config.py', 'ironic/cmd/api.py', 'ironic/cmd/conductor.py'], 'message': 'WIP:make sure conf is loaded first than "@periodics.periodic()"

Current, config.parse_args is called from our common/service.py
to load ironic.conf. However, service.py imports modules in below
sequence:

ironic.api.app -> ironic.api.hooks ->
ironic.conductor.rpcapi -> ironic.conductor.manager

So for such "@periodics.periodic(spacing=CONF.xxx)" code, it runs
before ironic.conf is loaded, that is the root cause these periodic
tasks always run with default spacing values even in case which are
overwritten with special values.

In this patch, we move config.parse_args to cmd/__init__.py, to make
sure the ironic.conf will be loaded first than other python modules
which are in the import list. Then, these
"@periodics.periodic(spacing=CONF.xxx)" codes run after the conf is
loaded, so these periodic spacing in conf will effect.

Now, this is a proposed draft fix for this issue, because I encountered
new issue with this solution, ironic-api and ironic-conductor works,
but only the ironic-dbsync command is not working, will raise
ArgsAlreadyParsedError exception, because it will run CONF.register_cli_opt
after 'config.parse_args' is called. So, just commits this patch here
for reviewing and getting more good ideas to fix this 'old' issue.

Change-Id: I545d4b40889ba66c3904f0f4a6f10e1a9532582a
Closes-Bug: #1562258
'}]
commit_message:
WIP:make sure conf is loaded first than "@periodics.periodic()"

Current, config.parse_args is called from our common/service.py
to load ironic.conf. However, service.py imports modules in below
sequence:

ironic.api.app -> ironic.api.hooks ->
ironic.conductor.rpcapi -> ironic.conductor.manager

So for such "@periodics.periodic(spacing=CONF.xxx)" code, it runs
before ironic.conf is loaded, that is the root cause these periodic
tasks always run with default spacing values even in case which are
overwritten with special values.

In this patch, we move config.parse_args to cmd/__init__.py, to make
sure the ironic.conf will be loaded first than other python modules
which are in the import list. Then, these
"@periodics.periodic(spacing=CONF.xxx)" codes run after the conf is
loaded, so these periodic spacing in conf will effect.

Now, this is a proposed draft fix for this issue, because I encountered
new issue with this solution, ironic-api and ironic-conductor works,
but only the ironic-dbsync command is not working, will raise
ArgsAlreadyParsedError exception, because it will run CONF.register_cli_opt
after 'config.parse_args' is called. So, just commits this patch here
for reviewing and getting more good ideas to fix this 'old' issue.

Change-Id: I545d4b40889ba66c3904f0f4a6f10e1a9532582a
Closes-Bug: #1562258

commit_message:
Fix event generation

This patch is about a serious bug in event generation. When passing in
an action object, we have been mistakenly using the action.id as the
obj_id. This is leading to the event generated cannot be filtered using
obj_id.

We don't have unit tests for the event module yet. That will be left in
a separate patch.

Change-Id: I542b55871845956c489b1832802bdc80deac210b
Closes-Bug: 1564936

Add name option to 'port set'

good feature for a user to have the ability to rename a port.

added in this patch.

commit_message:
WIP: conductor manager: apply console-log related methods

This patch applies methods for console logging to conductor.

- start_console_log() to do_node_deploy().
- stop_console_log() to destroy_node().
- get_console_log() and clear_console_log() as RPC endpoints.

NOTE: This is a proof-of-concept; unit tests will be added later.

Related-Bug: #1526368,#1553083
Change-Id: I628dfc98b65c6c5d6aea381442086403682974db

commit_message:
WIP: conductor utils: add start/stop console logging

This patch adds task.driver.console.(start|stop)_console_log() to
ironic.conductor.utils.node_power_action().
task.driver.console.start_console_log will be called on power-on,
and task.driver.console.stop_console_log on power-off.

NOTE: This is a proof-of-concept; unit tests will be added later.

Related-Bug: #1526368,#1553083
Change-Id: I8ba8c0735af3d43511eac7f935c4ab0121394e6a

commit_message:
Add MySQL int-test helper client

Adding a helper client for MySQL will enable int-tests
involving actual data operations.

The test_helper.py file was also modified to push
more boiler-plate code into the base class, as it has
become apparent that only one 'add' 'remove' and 'verify'
method is probably adecuate for most datastores (given
the right sane parameters). The Redis helper was also
cleaned up to use the new format.

Change-Id: Iff34ca0b922adc9eea8b3861b05adf0251109221
(cherry picked from commit 2b98c538624a55bda9abe304c08b19435869cbc6)
Co-Authored-By: Petr Malik <pmalik@tesora.com>
Co-Authored-By: Peter Stachowski <peter@tesora.com>

commit_message:
Bump alembic version to 0.8.4

This version of alembic was released in December 15, 2015
and include some bug fixes related to batch mode.
Batch mode is needed in case of SQLite usage.

Alembic bug 245 details:
http://alembic.readthedocs.org/en/latest/_sources/changelog.txt

Change-Id: I30a5c36efc00928d9ac60c34add0d73424cd72ef

commit_message:
Getting rid of task result proxies in workflow context

* Task result proxies were needed to be able to access
  task result as $.task_name. But this was deprecated in Mitaka
  in favor of using task() YAQL function. So it's time to get
  rid of complicated internal machinery before making further
  improvements

Change-Id: I9b8c1c9ac6e9561c6aa66151011ae2f7d906179a
Implements: blueprint mistral-remove-task-result-proxies

commit_message:
[api-ref] Changed the v2 parameters to lb_algorithms

The lb_method parameter has been changed to lb_algorithm in the v2
but still there were some places where the lb_method was mentioned
in the v2 version. This patch removes the lb_method and replaces
with lb_algorithm.

Change-Id: Iffac6db09a66b5c6391eca143d721293a69964c6
Closes-Bug: #1566138

commit_message:
Don't drop 'protocol' from client supplied security_group_rule dict

If protocol was present in the dict, but was None, then it was never
re-instantiated after being popped out of the dict. This later resulted
in KeyError when trying to access the key on the dict.

Change-Id: I4985e7b54117bee3241d7365cb438197a09b9b86
Closes-Bug: #1566327

commit_message:
Add instance create int-tests

Add generic integration tests for instance create.
Also moved some global constants to the base runner.

Note: Did some additional cleanup work on other test groups as well.
      Broke down some negative tests into more self-contained units.
      Added a comment string on tests that did not have it.
      Had to fix database_actions test to work for users defining
      hosts (like MySQL users).

Change-Id: I7c1413fa5742c276454e26ebbbeae8e02569a392
(cherry picked from commit aeadbfc974fc515ef85059c48277a56d0ec9037e)

commit_message:
Allow to upgrade nodes without re-provisioning

It's possible to reassign nodes from the upgrade environment to the seed
environment without re-provisioning. Use the `--roles` option to use
this feature:

    $ octane upgrade-node --no-provision \
        --roles=<role1>,<role2> <env> <node1> <node2>

Change-Id: I1fb88c6c7e0581034d8668373ecaa3ace2d085af
Depends-On: Iedb20a904e58f5b9a86eb47de8d8d317dc3cc61b

commit_message:
Enhance value check for option notify_on_state_change

oslo.config provides parameter choices for class cfg.StrOpt to
make sure user's input must be in the choices. Option
notify_on_state_change only allow three values, so let's use
parameter choices.

UpgradeImpact: option notify_on_state_change allows three values:
'vm_state', 'vm_and_task_state', None, default value is None.

Change-Id: I94b2a8ab2584a4a31ef9644ad4f614a15636de8d

commit_message:
Change get_root_helper_child_pid to stop when it finds cmd

get_root_helper_child_pid recursively finds the child of pid,
until it can no longer find a child. However, the intention is
not to find the deepest child, but to strip away root helpers.
For example 'sudo neutron-rootwrap x' is supposed to find the
pid of x. However, in cases 'x' spawned quick lived children of
its own (For example: ip / brctl / ovs invocations),
get_root_helper_child_pid returned those pids if called in
the wrong time.

Change-Id: I582aa5c931c8bfe57f49df6899445698270bb33e
Closes-Bug: #1558819

commit_message:
Ignore connection error when testing load balancer

In the integration test with Neutron Load Balancer, we sometimes fail to
connect to the Load Balancer when testing that the stack deployed
successfully. Let's ignore those errors so that we retry for a bit in
case it takes some time to be deployed.

Change-Id: Ic97bd83fe56dc52fb49848d93e40cb57d1550a1f
Closes-Bug: #1545587
(cherry picked from commit df73c1c79852f697208bed6dc59c6b790aeb8eb8)

commit_message:
Enable Ceilometer client to work with Keystone API v3

Keystone APIv3 supports domains, which means the same project name
may be used in different domains. Thus we need to use the ID not
the name when authenticating.

Change-Id: I29071e60c5f7f349e44a75063dd2b216c53dd1fd
Closes-Bug: #1525800

Add general_log to mariadb container and make heka collect it

Added general_log to ansible/roles/mariadb/templates/galera.cnf.j2
to improve mariadb logging.

mariadb is scaled.

http://paste.openstack.org/show/492852/

Closes-Bug: #1563668

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-04-05 16:02:07.000000000', 'files': ['ansible/roles/mariadb/tasks/start.yml'], 'message': 'Change waiting on mariadb.pid

Previously the code looked at mariadb.pid, but this seemed
flakey in function.  It seemed racey and prone to failure on
slower connections to a registry.  The original task was
extremely complex and it didnt really verify that the MariaDB
was ready to serve connections.  Use wait_for with a regex
instead.

Change-Id: I3aafac04f03639b08e0ef4d6a9c9e1a4499f000c
Closes-Bug: #1564278
'}]
commit_message:
Change waiting on mariadb.pid

Previously the code looked at mariadb.pid, but this seemed
flakey in function.  It seemed racey and prone to failure on
slower connections to a registry.  The original task was
extremely complex and it didnt really verify that the MariaDB
was ready to serve connections.  Use wait_for with a regex
instead.

Change-Id: I3aafac04f03639b08e0ef4d6a9c9e1a4499f000c
Closes-Bug: #1564278

commit_message:
delete verbose/redundant/deprecated text

the docs are a bit wordy in some places. our docs are confusing
enough:

- remove notification > polling in architecture page
- remove redundant Events filtering from event_types
- move shuffle/batch options to customisation page
- add http publisher
- remove db choices from architecture page, point to dbreco page
- remove db background referencing single database route
- remove warnings to say db might change, use api (obvious)
- remove stuff about Ceilometer is part Openstack but not tied to it
- move hbase configuration under common hbase section in install
- remove tox compatibility comments since it's > 2 years
- remove random non-devstack/historical text from devstack page

Change-Id: I76e4c7cf5bf94bb4423708ca88100fb23140fecd

commit_message:
Fix not supported error message

When execute "nova baremetal-node-create" command,
below error message is shown:
 ERROR (BadRequest): Command Not supported.
 Please use Ironic command port-create to perform this action. (HTTP 400)

Ironic command corresponds to nova baremetal-node-create is
not port-create, but node-create.
This patch set fixes this bug.

Change-Id: Id41b832f2b01c1848c224515fa70efec8a316ae9
Closes-bug: #1564870
